<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910429-0067</DOCNO><DOCID>910429-0067.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- TeleVideo Systems Inc.:   VDT and Computer Maker   Again Cuts Its Work Force</HL><DATE>04/29/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   TELV</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)</RE><LP>   TeleVideo Systems Inc. said it laid off 45 employees, orabout 18% of its work force, in its second personnel cutbackin a little more than a year.   The San Jose, Calif., maker of video-display terminals andpersonal computers said it was making more cuts because itintends to buy more of its parts from outside suppliers.</LP><TEXT>   Last year, when TeleVideo incurred a loss of $12.8million, the company laid off 60 employees and cut the pay ofsenior managers.</TEXT></DOC>